	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Magician Guide for Levels 1-40</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Quellbrer</a> | 
		            7/21/2003 9:53:37 AM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">OK.  This is for people who don't really want bad factions by kiling guards, bards,...etc.  OK, when I was lvl 1, I killed the stuff in West Freeport.  This lasted until lvl 3 and then I went further out into the Northern Desert of Ro.  Here you will find armadillos, young pumas, etc.  Kill these until you level to 4 and... YOU CAN GET YOUR PET SPELL!!!!  OK, now that you have a pet, go back to Nro Desert and keep killing stuff.  After the littler things in the zone get green, you can move on to bigger things, like large rattlesnakes, or gilla monsters.  Your pet is bada$$.  You nuke, and when mob starts to get close to you, send pet in.  Let him to the work and nuke if you want but heed my advice, if you want the best xp you can get when fighting with the pet, you want your pet to not take out more than 50% of the mob, if he does, you will only gain half the xp.  I dont think this really matters though because your pet heals real fast and is always ready to fight whenever you need him to, so the killing goes like twice as fast, therefore resulting in the same amount of xp.  OK, when I got too high for the grassy area of Nro, I then went to the desert area.  Many things to kill here, such as desert tarantulas, sand scarabs, pumas.. and so on.  Remember to get your new pet every 4 levels =).  Rely on your pet!!!  He is awesome and will save your butt so many times...  When you are about lvl 15-16, I suggest moving on out further to the Oasis of Marr.  I found that grouping up and fighting crocs is some of the best xp for these levels.  Crocs will start giving low xp at about 18, so I then went to Highpass Hold.  There are hardly any people in this zone, so if you wanna group up it sucks, but if you cant find a group in Highold Pass, then you can always go to Highkeep.  It's right next to HH, and if you can, try and group up and kill goblins.  Most people will tell you that you are too low, but it's worth a try.  Well, when I finally hit lvl 20 off of orcs in HH, It was off to HK.  This is like the greatest xp ever for levels 20-35.  I stayed for 15 levels and it was so awesome.  There are always groups of people in HK on, so finding one is no problem.  Loot isn't that bad either, up to 4pp on some goblins.  At 35-36, I suggest going to Overthere, not bad xp but loot isn't that good.  But it is generally a good place to level since there are many people here in this zone also.  When I hit, the big 40, I went to Dreadlands and right now I am fighting in KC (Karnor's Castle), a zone in the middle of DL, fighting Dravlogs, Call of the Sithers, and more.  Make sure that you always give your pet the swords from your Sword of Runes Spell and give him Burnout II.  If you want to stay in Dreadlands though, you can kill dravlogs, spiders, voracious brutes, and much more things.  Once again, this zone has plenty of people to group with so finding one should be a breeze.  Hope this helps for all you mages out there with a problem.  And here is just my general opinion on the pets.  Earth is very good, with a great defense and has the most hp, and it can root, which also saves your butt like a 1000 times from overnuking.  But the downside of Earth is that it is slow.  Water is an all around pet, has decent hp, and can cast a Direct Damage spell on the mob (I don't know for how much damage, but it's something!!)  Water is a good all-around pet.  Air can cast invisibility, but I find this very pathetic as it cannot help in combat.  The good thing about air is that it can stun mobs.. it's hp is kinda low.  And the fire pet, well, this pet has a Damage Shield that hurts the mob everytime he is hit.  He can casts a direct damage spell also on the mob (like water pet), but the hp is low just like air's hp.  I have tested this though, no matter what people say hits for harder, I found that all of the pets hit for the same amount of damage at their certain level.  Say you have an earth pet at lvl 16, and a fire pet at lvl 16.  They will both hit for the SAME AMOUNT OF DAMAGE, the only difference is in the hp's and the abilities.  Remember to always keep your pet buffed up and treat it with love, for it is your melee!!!
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
